name: NYDailyNews
text:
Maryland man, Ibrahim Bouaichi, 33 — suspected of raping a woman and later killing her while he awaited trial — was released from jail because of coronavirus.

He seems to have shot himself when cops caught up to him, and was reportedly in grave condition.

Andy Dick filed a lawsuit against his New Orleans puncher  David Hale, who he claims caused “serious, permanent and disabling injuries.”

text:
The district attorney for Aurora, Colo., is going to investigate the Colorado cops who handcuffed Black girls over a car that wasn’t stolen.

The cops were looking for a stolen vehicle, which was a motorcycle, clearly not an SUV.

The Nets secured themselves a playoff seed with their win over the Kings.

The only thing left to decide is who their playoff opponent will be: the Milwaukee Bucks or the Toronto Raptors.

text:
At 83, Dame Shirley Bassey is working on new album, referred to as a "grand finale."

Details about the upcoming opus is still under wraps but will be dedicated to her fans and include brand new material written especially for the singer.
